data.description: BALANCE OF MORTGAGE ASSUMABLE AT 3.5%.  Gorgeously Restored Twin-Home in Historical West Germantown! Welcome to 269 W Harvey St. This tranquil 6BD/3 full, 2 1/2 BA home sits atop a hill overlooking a private, tree lined street and is truly a MUST see. Upon ascending the front staircase, you are welcomed onto the large, cement front porch/deck fenced and completely private; creating a peaceful spot for morning coffee and relaxation. As you enter through the front door, you will immediately be in awe of the tall 9 ft Coffered ceiling, warm, hardwood flooring, and stately feel of the first floor. The rooms have been divided with purpose and each flow easily into the next. The first room to the left through the French doors is the living room. Complete with a custom made gas fireplace, crown molding and a large window offering a generous amount of natural light. To the right you will enter the large, formal dining room featuring a bay window and plenty of room for entertaining. The chef-style kitchen features Granite counter-top, timeless backsplash and top quality safe energy Samsung SS appliances including: French door refrigerator, stove, dishwasher, and microwave. Not to mention, the interior kitchen top and bottom lighting. The kitchen provides access to the back porch, spacious, wood deck, and grand, fully fenced, backyard. There is also a powder room on the first floor. The second floor is home to the owner's suite plus an additional bedroom and hallway bath. The primary suite is complete with a sitting room, walk-in closet and a spa-like bathroom with both a shower and Jacuzzi tub. The third floor features 3 additional, spacious bedrooms and 1 full bath with upgraded features. The finished basement is a complete living/sleeping area within itself. An additional family room/living space plus a bedroom occupies the finished basement. Also there is a half bath and full laundry space you do not see in most homes! Situated in West Germantown, historical landmarks, vast parks, coffee shops and dining are in great supply. Also nearby neighborhoods like Chestnut Hill, Roxborough/Manayunk and East Falls provide more restaurant opportunities as well as access to the Schuylkill River Path. Commuting is also a breeze with the home's close proximity to major highways and public transportation. Does this spectacular home sound like your style? If so, add it to your MUST SEE list today!
